data.title: Neinor Homes reports €122mn net income in FY25 after biggest M&A in Spanish residential sector last decade.
data.description: In Madrid, as of February 26, 2026, Neinor Homes closed the fiscal year 2025 with impressive operational and financial achievements. Excluding the impact of acquiring a 79.2% stake in AEDAS, Neinor notarized a total of 2,901 housing units during the year. Of these, 1,891 were part of the fully owned portfolio, while 1,010 belonged to the Asset Management business. The total revenues for 2025 amounted to €697 million. Borja García-Egotxeaga, the CEO of Neinor Homes, described the year as transformational for the company. For more details, the full story can be accessed on Benzinga.com.
